\begin_layout Title
Status Needs under Uncertainty
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract

\shape italic
We develop a model for status under a stochastic environment where consumer
 anxieties from non-uniform uncertainties are eased with status consumption.
 Using insights from the Prospect Theory, we view status consumption as
 a means to achieve security of one's position in a wealth hierarchy - explainin
g how the asymmetries in information and uncertainty influence consumer
 utility.
 The economic value of status consumption and the policy implications for
 taxation using a normative framework for status competitions are discussed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
