LatexCommand ref
reference "sec:Model"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
 The sportsperson - for instance - may bear a risk-seeking behaviour in
 the short-term but might plan to be more risk-averse in the future.
 Similarly, an academic who does not expect a windfall in the short-term
 may plan to be more risk-seeking in the long-term while the risk-profile
 of the investor may lie somewhere in between.
 The consumer with different risk-aversion levels all perform a function
 in the economy and the extent to which they could compete each other is
 always limited by resource constraints.
 Further, since the risk-aversion levels depend on occupational structures,
 the subjective perception of the idiosyncratic risk in one's relative wealth
